## ‚ùì Frequently Asked Questions

### Can I use this software for commercial purposes?
Yes, the MIT License allows commercial use without any restrictions.

### Do I need to open source my modifications?
No, you can keep your modifications private. However, you must include the copyright notice and license.

### Can I change the license for my fork?
You can add additional restrictions in your fork, but you cannot remove the MIT License requirements for the original code.

### Do I need to attribute the original authors?
Yes, you must include the copyright notice and permission notice in all copies or substantial portions of the software.

### Can I use the project name or logo?
The MIT License does not grant trademark rights. Please contact us for permission to use the project name or logo.

